            "text": " where  $z = \\zeta_n^m$ . Let  $d = \\frac{n}{(n,m)}$ . Recall that  $(\\mathbb{Z}/n\\mathbb{Z})^{\\times} = M \\cdot N$  where  $M$  and  $N$  are given in   Lemma 3.1. Note that  $z = \\zeta_n^m$  is a primitive *d*-th root of 1 since  $\\left(d, \\frac{m}{(n,m)}\\right) = 1$ . Hence,",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
